                <h1>Cubism: Redefining Art through Abstract Perspectives</h1>
                <p>Cubism is an innovative art movement that emerged in the early 20th century, primarily founded by artists Pablo Picasso and Georges Braque. Characterized by fragmented forms, multiple perspectives, and abstraction, cubism revolutionized traditional representation in art. By reimagining subjects in geometric shapes, it invites viewers to engage with reality differently.</p>
